<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4031: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-06T22:00:00+01:00">February 6, 1932—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 6—5:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>12. Text of communiqué issued after today’s private meeting of Council
                            referred to in my 10<note n="78" xml:id="d264fn78">Not printed.</note>
                            follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The members of the Council other than the parties met at 4:30 to
                                    hold an exchange of views. They were of the opinion that in the
                                    present circumstances since the steps of the powers brought to
                                    the notice of the Council on February 2nd are not terminated a
                                    debate on the Sino-Japanese dispute at the public meeting today
                                    would not be advisable.”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_WHR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>